FBIS4-11419 "drlat082_a_94009" FBIS-LAT-94-082 Daily Report 26 Apr 1994 CARIBBEAN Cuba Minister States Need for More Access To Markets Minister States Need for More Access To Markets FL2604152994 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 0900 GMT 26 Apr 94 FL2604152994 Havana Radio Rebelde Network Spanish BFN [Text] Ernesto Melendez, Cuba's minister of foreign investment and economic cooperation, has stated that Cuba has to have greater access to Latin American and Caribbean markets. During the 15th ministerial conference of the ECLA [Economic Commission for Latin America], Melendez pointed out that ECLA is the appropriate forum for taking the first steps to incorporate Cuba into the region.
